data.title: List of countries by left-hand, right-hand and center-hand traffic
data.meta_description: See also: Left- and right-hand traffic (fictional) This is a list of countries in the fictional world by either left-hand, right-hand or center-hand traffic. NOTE: Please put the countries in alphabetical order.

South Aslana officially drove on the right until 1999, even after the South ceased to exist due to the conversion of road traffic to the left being expensive and the crash of the Aslanian economy after the war. The Sixfen Islands Special Administrative Territory (SISAT) drives on the right, due to the 30 year, 3 phase sovereignty plan after the occupation by the end of the 1988 war that allows SISAT to continue to keep their right-hand traffic until independence where they will be allowed to choose for themselves. The Sixfenese public is in favor of keeping their right-hand traffic.
